                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13940.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister</gloss> to Mexico to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-29T14:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 29, 1914, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>227. Zapata arrived November 27: he refused to come to the National Palace to
                    receive a manifestation of the people and stayed at a very modest hotel in the
                    suburbs. General Angeles arrived yesterday with the advance guard but is waiting
                    for Villa to properly enter the capital. A general order from Villa is published
                    according full guaranties to all, any wrong to be punished by death. General
                    situation surprisingly good.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
